Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Databases Engineer position with Grafana Labs. I bring over three years of professional experience in distributed systems, observability, and cloud-native infrastructure, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade distributed systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a distributed multi-tenant orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph that coordinates concurrent tool execution across 1,000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, reliable coordination, and safe execution in a microservices environment. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering distributed tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks to monitor behavior, debug production failures, and track quality metrics over time. This work directly mirrors the operational responsibilities of the Mimir squad: building, operating, and maintaining critical systems while owning their reliability, performance, and availability. I also optimized performance and scalability by tuning prompt routing and concurrency, reducing latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% — demonstrating the kind of efficiency-focused engineering that's essential when operating telemetry databases at scale. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with multi-cloud distributed systems. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with a focus on reliability, performance, and availability, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts, ensuring operational stability in production. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the Databases team's core engineering responsibilities: driving projects from initial idea to production, participating in on-call rotations, and operating distributed systems at scale across major cloud providers.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in distributed model training, high-performance computing, and cloud-native deployment — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for distributed model training and fine-tuning at scale. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from data preparation and training runs to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face — ensuring both performance and secure, efficient model serving in a cloud-native environment. This experience working with distributed systems on HPC infrastructure directly parallels the work of operating Mimir, Loki, Tempo, and Pyroscope as multi-tenant distributed systems on Kubernetes across AWS, GCP, and Azure. Beyond building the systems myself, I have experience writing and reviewing design documents, shepherding releases, and collaborating with teammates in a fully remote setup — directly mirroring the code review, design discussion, and follow-the-sun on-call responsibilities central to this role.

I have always been passionate about open source and transparency, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Grafana Labs' mission to build a sustainable business around open source projects and help customers achieve success with their observability goals. The company's commitment to "progress over perfection" and "respectfully empowered" culture resonates deeply with my own approach to engineering: ship value iteratively, own your work, and help your team thrive. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

